(27, 1, '27.jpg', 'BATTLE FOR TOP FOUR!  Brighton set to cause an upset against Tottenham', '\n<p>\n   Five games to go and the race for who gets the fourth spot still tarries with the likes of Tottenham Hotspur and Chelsea go into action this mid week. Tottenham who are seven points clear off Chelsea in the fifth position will look to increase their tally to ten as they go  head to head with Brighton this evening after their awful performance against the current champions, Manchester city on Saturday in Wembley. The match which Tottenham needed at least a draw to stay safe in their bid for champions league spot was brought to shambles as they were well beaten Infront of their home fans. \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   With the dramatic comeback against Southampton, Chelsea\'s confidence in winning games were back as they look to mount pressure on Tottenham this Thursday for fourth spot as they take on a resurgence Burnley side who are looking to secure Europa spot. A brace from Olivier Giroud and a superb finish from Eden Hazard saw Conte\'s men steal away all three points from the saints on Saturday. They will look to keep up that fine form as they travel to Burnley to get all three points. The question now is, who will finish fourth? Well, only time will tell.\n</p>\n', 4, '2018-04-17 08:47:53', 'APPROVED'),
(28, 1, '28.jpg', 'BIG BLOW FOR BAYERN MUNICH GOING INTO THE CHAMPIONS LEAGUEðŸ˜±ðŸ˜±', '\n<p>\n   News reporting late last night has it that key man, Arturo Vidal is out of the season due to a major set back in training. The 30 year old Chilean centre midfielder who has scored six goals with 17  caps will miss the cracker going into next week champions league against Real Madrid.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   According to the manager, &quot;he just slipped and fell during training&quot;. This injury will make way for players like Hernandez to fill in that spot and hope to get something going into the semi\'s against Real.\n</p>\n', 4, '2018-04-18 03:09:50', 'APPROVED'),
(29, 1, '29.jpg', 'HUGE BOOST FOR BRAZIL GOING INTO THE WORLD CUPðŸ˜€ðŸ˜€', '\n<p>\n   The Brazilian forward and PSG talisman, Neymar is set to return to training mid may after suffering a broken foot in February. The forward who missed the second leg champions league cracker against Real Madrid following a set back against Marseille in their league cup is likely to feature in the world cup coming up in less than two months.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   This is as a result of his final examination on the foot that is scheduled to hold May 17. According to reports, Neymar is hopeful of returning back to action following the world cup in view but in doubt for his club side as they will play their final league Game two days before the supposed date.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   According to him, he is communicating well with his coach in Brazil and the technical coordinator, giving them updates on his recovery.\n</p>\n', 4, '2018-04-18 06:01:54', 'APPROVED'),
(30, 4, '30.jpg', 'IMPORTANT UPDATE - Tips on smashing UNN Post Utme', '\n<p>\n   As we count down the months, you will notice that, we have not less than 3 months towards UNN post utme examination. And there are some tips you need to know very well in the course of preparing for the very examination. These tips include:\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   1. Nature of the examination : This is the most complicated issue facing many aspirants every year. Someone might be reading and studying quite right but not in the area of examination concentration. Some even study NECO and WAEC past questions while preparing for the very post utme examination without knowing they are missing the road. Now, ask your self, how exactly does UNN post utme examination looks like?... Does it covers some o level past questions?... Do they repeat questions from past questions?... What are the exactly cogent reading materials that are suitable for preparation of UNN post utme examination???...  And many more questions you need to be asking your self concerning the nature of the examination... Self interrogation is part of learning because through that, you will get to the pathway of resolving your problems. So, the greatest threat and cause of most aspirants\' failure is the lack of knowledge concerning the nature of the examination they are preparing for. Now, based on the subheading, an answer to this trauma is studying jamb past questions.... When I said, studying jamb past questions, I didn\'t mean that you should go and cram the answers; you are being advised to study with understandings and be able to answer a similar question anywhere found. Know it that the nature of UNN post utme examination is 70% jamb past questions, 20% general knowledge on the four subjects you are writing and 10% UNN post utme past questions....\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   To be continued.... \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Don\'t forget to hit the like button. And also leave your comments in the comment box for future analysis...\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Best regards!!! \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   From: Lionel Richard Nnabuike\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-18 07:57:21', 'APPROVED'),
