(37, 7, NULL, 'Be INSPIRED towards your DESIRE', '\n<p>\n   âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨ðŸ’¡ðŸ’¡âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž _*In Life, one tends to face challenges. These challenges determines your success in Life. There is no great man in this world that never encountered challenges. A person becomes a genius because He is focused despite all the forces that tends to stymie Him from achieving success.*_\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž *Some people become frustrated just because they think that their suffering due to challenges appears too much to be bearable. But Let me ask you this question,* _*&quot;Have you moved out to the Larger Society to enquire about the status of destitute and Handicaps in the society?.*_ *There are many people who don\'t even have hope of eating today except through alms giving and Miracle.*\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž  *More so, many students tend to become bemoan just because they failed in an examination. Do you know that someone in this world can\'t even pay for His/Her school fees. Last year, an undergraduate committed suicide just because she failed a course. That\'s undoubtedly exasperating, what if she knew that there are millions of people who are writing JAMB just to come up to that level(undergraduate level).*\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž *It is High time you knew that &quot;It is your Decision; not your condition; that determines your Destination. Many people quits their ambition because they are discouraged and rebuked by their Friends.*\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’« _But I want to tell you that:_\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž _*JORDAN who is today recorded as the best basket ball player was chased out of His basket ball team in His college. Despite this, He never hesitated to move on.*_\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž *I always advice people to choose what they want(their goals) and tenaciously work towards it. You may fail, but let your effort increase as you progress. It doesn\'t matter your age, what matters is your perseverance and determination.*\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n    ðŸ’Ž _*I don\'t actually believe that their is any apex that can\'t be unraveled if there is an effective preparation to provoke unusual transformations.*_\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž *While reading your text books, you will discover that there is always a development and new theories are being established as the year egresses. In science Dalton\'s atomic postulate all became void due to discoveries by different scientists. Most of the scientists were actually thought the theory but they never settled with it. They believed that there is a great thought that is embedded in them.*\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž _You will discover that development comes when_ *&quot;IMPOSSIBILITY&quot;* IS UNRAVELED.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   _*Napoleon Hills once said that &quot;whatever the mind can perceive;that it can achieve&quot;.*_\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž *Create that plan that seems impossible and leave a legacy for the development of the world.*\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   *Thank you for reading.* \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’Ž *Better days ahead.*\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ðŸ’«ðŸ’«ðŸ’«ðŸ’«ðŸ’¥ðŸ’¥ðŸ’«ðŸ’«ðŸ’«ðŸ’«\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-18 23:24:13', 'APPROVED'),
(39, 1, '39.jpg', 'Mission Accomplished as Chelsea sets up a Mouthwatering final against Manchester unitedðŸ™ŒðŸ™ŒðŸ™Œ', '\n<p>\n   Two goals in the second half was enough to see Chelsea through to the finals. Goals from Olivier Giroud and Alvaro Morata did the job in Wembley on Sunday afternoon to give Conte hope of winning a silver ware 2017/2018 season.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Chelsea started the brighter of the two teams in the first ten minutes of the first half with Eden hazard and Willian taking shots from outside the area. The momentum built in when Willian\'s long ball hit the wood work from a short pass from hazard. It ended with no goal to report as the referee blew his half time whistle.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The game came alive 28 secs of the second half with a glorious goal from Giroud when he picked up a loose ball from hazard and dribbled past three defenders to give Chelsea the lead. The second came in from the substitute Alvaro Morata scoring with a beautiful header from close range to give Chelsea a two goal lead.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Southampton kept asking all the questions Infront of goal as they look to get something out of the game but all proved abortive. The game wrapped up and sets up a super final against Manchester united in Wembley.\n</p>\n', 4, '2018-04-22 12:08:41', 'APPROVED'),
(40, 1, '40.jpg', 'Swansea city thrashed by current champions, Manchester city 5 nil at the EtihadðŸ˜±ðŸ˜±', '\n<p>\n   Having declared champions last weekend with Manchester united losing at home to a relegating westbrom, Manchester city were not satisfied as they destroyed a struggling Swansea side five goals to nil at the Etihad on Sunday.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Guardiola\'s hunger to win every game was not lacking in this fixture as they made every moment count from the beginning of the game till the end. David Silva opened the scoring while sterling doubled the lead in the first 20 minutes to give Manchester city the lead in the first half.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Hopes of Swansea coming back in the second half was left in anguish as De bruyne fired home a superb strike from open play. Things didn\'t go as plan for the away side as they conceded a penalty in which Bernando Silva converted through a rebound by Gabriel Jesus. The fifth goal came in few minutes to the End of the game when Jesus headed a home a sublime pass from Yaya toure.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   With four games remaining, the current champions still looking hungry to set a record of 100 points in a season and everything going for the lads. Congrats to the champions.\n</p>\n', 4, '2018-04-22 13:39:26', 'APPROVED'),
(41, 1, '41.jpg', '&quot;I have no issues with Mourinho&quot;- Conte claims as his side book spot for Fa Cup final in W', '\n<p>\n   Conte and Mourinho have clashed publicly on numerous occasions, but the Chelsea boss insists that any issues the pair might have had are firmly in the past.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   â€œWith Jose, we have clarified the situation. This is the most important thing,\" Conte explained to reporters after the final whistle.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \"There is not a problem between him and I. I think this final is a game between two great teams: Manchester United and Chelsea.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \"For sure, in my mind, I can tell you that we played last season in the final and arrived as favourites against Arsenal. This season, we are arriving not as favourites. But, as you know very well, we lost the final despite being favourites in my mind.\n</p>\n', 4, '2018-04-22 14:18:43', 'APPROVED'),
(43, 7, '43.jpg', 'Clarification on what the president said about the Nigerian youths', '\n<p>\n   Clarification of the speech made by the President of the Republic of Nigeria - Mohammed Buhari \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Some times we the humans should learn how to avoid following crowd mentality because it is part of maturity... Based on the trending issue making viral waves on social media concerning what our president in the person of Mohammed Buhari said about the Nigerian youth... If we can understand simple English, we can not in any way misinterpret his candid speech... And mind you that he is a nationwide icon and for the fact that he is the president, everybody will like to assimilate personal meaning into his speech whether positive or negative... Just like the very day he made his first speech as the president of this country, he said : I\'m for everybody and for nobody... This simple sentence is not something hard to understand in the sense that he\'s for the people that voted for him and also for the people that didn\'t vote for him... What is hard to understand in that statement??? Now From what he said concerning the youth of this country, Mr.  President simply said: Nigerian youths are after already made things... Nobody wants to work and majority depend on oil products of the country... That nobody wants to work his way out... And if this continues this way, what would be the fate of the upcoming generation??? and this might render the upcoming generation into laziness... And not that the Nigerian youths are lazy... Let\'s try to understand something first before cooking its meanings!!! And know it that this is the era of politics and election... This character assassination is a way of bringing bad governance into Baba\'s government... Please, let the Nigerian youth should not be used to create enmity  between the ruling government and the ruled... Thanks \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Best regards!!! \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   God bless Nigeria...\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-22 19:45:12', 'APPROVED'),
(44, 7, '44.jpg', 'YOWERI OF UGANDA BLAST BUHARI ...', '\n<p>\n   YOWERI MUSEVENI OF UGANDA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Buhari is the most useless President that ever happens to that great country Nigeria... A leader should not expose his citizens, Nigeria is a great and an outstanding country in Africa because of the youth of that country.... our people have an Africanized social life all over Africa is because Nigerian youth put their full hardworking efforts look at the movie industry and most outstanding the music industry.... Buhari can never outgrow the slave and master mentality, He keeps talking bad about his people any time he makes a trip. Britain is there to exploit and steal just what they are known for. He seizes to understand that Britain created that country and gave it all the flaws that will never make it grow beyond a limit. Nigerians will vote him out it is obvious there is nothing Britain can do about it... If he Tries to annul or rig the election he will face a wide loss of legitimacy Nigerians are patiently waiting to send him back to retirement...\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-22 20:34:15', 'APPROVED'),
(45, 4, '45.jpg', 'Catchment Area and Educational less developed states', '\n<p>\n   About catchment Area and Educational less developed states.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ELDS are states in Nigeria which are considered to be\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   disadvantaged when it comes to gaining high quality\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Education. This states are always given preferential\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   treatment during admission exercise.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The Federal government has designed the Admission quota of each University to favor the Educationally Less developed states.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   This means that candidates from the ELDS have a better\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   chance of gaining admission into the University after\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   scaling through the Universityâ€™s Minimum requirements\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   (Mostly Cut off Marks).\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Note: ELDS only applies to a federal government owned\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   University and they occupy 20% out of the total carrying\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   capacity of the Course or school in question.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   List Of ELDS States In Nigeria...\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The Following states are considered by the Federal\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Government of Nigeria as being among the Educationally\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   less developed states and they are:\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   ELDS STATES:\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   1. ADAMAWA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   2. BAUCHI\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   3. BAYELSA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   4. BENUE\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   5. BORNO\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   6. CROSS RIVER\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   7. EBONYI\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   8. GOMBE\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   9. JIGAWA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   10. KADUNA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   11. KANO\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   12. KATSINA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   13. KEBBI\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   14. KOGI\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   15. KWARA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   16. NASARAWA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   17. NIGER\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   18. PLATEAU\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   19. RIVERS\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   20. SOKOTO\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   21. TARABAv\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   22. YOBE\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   23. ZAMFARA\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Other ones not find in the list are not considered as an ELDS State.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   In a nutshell......\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   if you didn\'t get up to merit cut off mark  but you got your state cut off mark, you must be admitted in primary list........UNN primary list is the combination of catchment area cutoff mark, ELDS cut off mark (Educational less Developed State) and Merit cutoff mark ............\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Every State have where they fall in any of above 3 cut off marks...\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Don\'t be sad when you see someone that scored higher... what you should be after is whether he/she is from your\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   State of origin......\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   For example if you are from IMO state and you got 230 and you are the only person that applied for a particular course from that state, you must be admitted (easiest admission) ... If another person with the same 230 applied the same course but the person is from a state where many people from that state scored higher, there\'s a big possibility of that person not been admitted.....\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The reason why UNN has 3 special cutoff mark is that UNN is a federal school and so all candidates from the 36 States must be represented to respect the federal character written in 1999 Constitution as amended..........\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   So asking about another person\'s score once it comes out,\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   is worthless because all the States don\'t have the same cut off mark or quota.......\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Someone from Zamfara state can be admitted into Medsug with 265 while someone from IMO with 265 will not be admitted in the same Medsug..........\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   I will explain more after the postutme examination results\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   are out, I will post about supplementary form secrets, and\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   all the processes that will help you gain admission this\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   year... So don\'t be afraid of your performance...\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   So for those that are still yet to get the UNN post utme PDF Past Questions and the hard copy should please chat me up...\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   08134690374\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Best regards!!!\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-23 04:20:56', 'APPROVED'),
(46, 1, '46.jpg', 'SALAH WINS PFAðŸ˜ŠðŸ˜ŠðŸ˜Š', '\n<p>\n   Salah also wins BBC readers vote\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   BBC Sport readers were asked to select their winner from the six-man shortlist and the Liverpool forward got 76% of the votes.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Coming a distant second was De Bruyne, who took 14% of the votes.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Manchester United goalkeeper De Gea was third with 6%, while Spurs striker Kane picked up 3% of the selections.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   De Bruyne\'s team-mates took up the final two spots, with Silva on 1% and Sane failing to win a single vote.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Mohamed Salah is the seventh Liverpool FC player to be crowned PFA Player of the Year\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Terry McDermott 1979â€“80\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Kenny Dalglish 1982â€“83\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Ian Rush 1983â€“84\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   John Barnes 1987â€“88\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Steven Gerrard 2005â€“06\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Luis Suarez 2013â€“14\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   He is the first Egyptian to lift the honour \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Liverpool will pay about Â£48m for the midfielder if Leipzig end up 7th or below. That rises to Â£52.75m should they qualify for the Europa League, which they are on course to do, and Â£59m if they earn a place in the Champions League. (Paul Joyce)\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Liverpool tried to bring forward the agreement in January, only for Leipzig to counter by asking for Trent Alexander-Arnold as part of any early deal. That request was dismissed. (Paul Joyce)\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Salah attended the award ceremony with Liverpool captain Jordan Henderson, a request the Egyptian made as he wanted to share the honour with his team-mates. (Telegraph)\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Salah: â€œTo break the Premier League record is something huge in England and all over in the world. There are still three games to go. I want to break this record and also break the one for a 42-game season.â€ By @_ChrisBascombe\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Klopp did not attend because he is preparing for the Champions League semi-final first leg with Salahâ€™s former club, Roma, but he asked the senior members of his scouting and recruitment team to accompany Salah as he collected the honour. (Telegraph)\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Salah is also a contender for the Football Writersâ€™ award, announced on May 1. (Telegraph)\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Henderson: â€œAs a person, heâ€™s a really good person, heâ€™s humble and genuine and he fits in really well with the group.â€\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Jordan Henderson paid tribute to PFA Playersâ€™ Player of the Year Mohamed Salah by saying his teammate has been â€˜amazingâ€™ since the day he joined Liverpool, writes @SamWiIliams\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Henderson: â€œHe was amazing in training, amazing in the pre-season games and heâ€™s just continued that form throughout the season. Heâ€™s been fantastic, on and off the field.â€\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Henderson: â€œHeâ€™s always doing work behind the scenes, always in the gym doing little bits here and there and working on his shooting in training, always working hard on what he needs to do for the team first and foremost, but then his goal tally speaks for itself really.â€\n</p>\n', 4, '2018-04-23 07:26:11', 'APPROVED'),
(47, 5, '47.jpg', 'Official date for second semester academic session', '\n<p>\n   This is to bring to the notice of the general public that the university community - university of Nigeria nsukka has officially begun her second semester academic session on 23rd of April 2018.... But lectures will fully begin on 1st of May 2018... The students, the academic staff units and the non academic staff units are thereby advised to adhere to the new resumption of academic session.\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-26 10:58:15', 'APPROVED'),
(48, 3, '48.jpg', 'New DVC emerges for UNEC', '\n<p>\n   Professor Edith Nwosu (Associate Dean Student Affairs UNEC) has been elected new Deputy Vice-Chancellor of the University of Nigeria, Enugu Campus (UNEC). She beat her closest rival, Professor Nwachukwu 289 to 23 votes at the Senate election held this morning at Nsukka Campus.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Professor Charles Igwe was re-elected Deputy Vice-Chancellor (Administration) with a 298 to 9 votes ahead of Professor Echezona.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   In the same vein, Professor James Ogbonna was re-elected Deputy Vice-Chancellor (Academic) with 291 to 19 votes ahead of Professor Urama.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Details of other Senate proceedings will be published subsequently and accordingly.\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-26 11:11:12', 'APPROVED'),
(49, 7, '49.jpg', 'IGP Fails To Appear Before Senate Over Melaye&rsquo;s Arrest, Insecurity issues', '\n<p>\n   The Inspector General of Police, Ibrahim Kpotun Idris has failed to appear before the Senate on Wednesday, to explain the circumstances surrounding the travails of Senator Dino Melaye.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The non-appearance of the IGP became clear when Deputy Senate leader, Bala Ibnâ€™Nallah moved that order 17 of Senate rules which deals with the invitation of IGP be considered.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   In utter dismay, Naâ€™Allah said, the Special Adviser to the President on National Assembly matters, Senator Ita Enang has told him that the IGP has travelled to Bauchi with President Buhari.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n         Senate President, Dr. Bukola Saraki asked the Chairman of Senate Committee on Police Affairs, Abu Ibrahim, to explain what happened to the invitation of IGP.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Abu said, the IGP has sent his DIG operations, but Saraki declined, saying it is IGP that was invited.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   â€œDid we invite the DIG or IGP?,â€ Saraki asked.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Senators who spoke were unanimous that the IGP lacked respect for the Senate.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   More details coming soon....  Check back\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-26 12:05:28', 'APPROVED'),
(51, 7, '51.jpg', '&ldquo;For The Last 48 Hours, I Have Not Been Able To Reach IGP,&rdquo; &ndash; Saraki', '\n<p>\n   Senate President Bukola Saraki during plenary on Wednesday lamented at the attitude of the Inspector General of Police (IGP), Ibrahim Idris saying he hasnâ€™t been able to reach the IGP for the last 48hours.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Saraki said this after the Senate resolved to invite the IGP to brief the plenary over the recent killings in Benue, and the arrest of Senator Dino Melaye.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   â€œToday, Senator Akume is not here because of what happened in Benue. I wanted to take the matter today so that he can be here today to take the issue. This is also about law and order and as such we must all condemn this action. This is not where we should be dispensing our energy on.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   â€œIt is important that the IGPâ€¦ even me for the last 48 hours, I have not been able to reach the IGP. I have tried so many times to find out, what is the situation. I think that is not a disrespect to me as an individual, but to this institution,â€ Saraki said.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n        He said further that collaboration with the legislature is essential to create enabling an environment for peace in the nation. He added that excesses from any quarters must be contained in the interest of Nigerians.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   â€œThese excesses must be contained in the interest of all of us. We are about to start elections and if these excesses of those who are meant to be responsible for providing law and order are not contained, it will be a great concern in this country. Therefore, those who are directly responsible need to take up that responsibility. â€œWe cannot talk about security without collaboration with the legislature. This kind of attitude must stop if we truly want to sustain and create enabling environment,â€ Saraki said.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The Senate subsequently adjourned plenary to visit their colleague, Dino Melaye who is currently on admission at the national hospital.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Saraki has led about 40 other Senators on the visit. Nine of the Senators including the Saraki were allowed to see Melaye who is now in the Intensive Care Unit of the National Hospital.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The embattled Senator Dino Melaye according to a statement by police authorities on Tuesday jumped from the moving police vehicle which was conveying him to a court in Lokoja, Kogi State allegedly in a bid to escape from police custody.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Melaye was expected to be interrogated by the police in connection with the allegation that he armed some thugs and in relation to other criminal activities.\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-26 12:10:59', 'APPROVED'),
(52, 7, '52.jpg', 'President Buhari \'s Impeachment Process Currently Ongoing', '\n<p>\n   Early this month, the President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, Mohammadu Buhari (GCFR) gave an authorization for the release if $496 million dollars which was used by the Nigerian Defence Sector to purchase a Fighter Helicopter. Last week, Nigerian Lawmakers reacted to that and summoned the Nigerian President, CBN Governor, & the Nigerian Defence Minister to the Senate.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Yesterday, Thursday 26th April, 2018, some senators have called for the Impeachment of Mr. Buhari with immediate effect.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Moving a motion at the Senate on Thursday, Sen. Matthew Uroghide, Edo State, pointed out that President Buhariâ€™s move was a violation of the constitution and thus, he should face the consequences.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   He encouraged the Nigerian Senate to invoke Section 143 ( which provides for the removal of the president from office) to start the impeachment process of the president.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Immediately, Sen. Chukwuka Utazi seconded the position spoke in support of the move.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \"This is clearly an impeachable offense\"... he stated.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Meanwhile, the President of Nigeria in his explanation letter conveyed at the Senate on Wednesday, pointed out that he gave the approval with the belief that the senate would back him up.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   His letter reads thus:\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   â€œI wish to draw the attention of the Senate to the ongoing security emergencies in the nation.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   These challenges were discussed with the state governors and subsequently at the meeting of the National Economic Council on the 14th of December 2017 where a resolution was passed with the council approving that up to $1 billion may be released and utilised from the Excess Crude Account to address the situation.â€\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-27 14:00:48', 'APPROVED'),
(53, 7, NULL, 'Home of Nwodo, President of Ohanaeze Ndigbo bombed', '\n<p>\n   The country home of the embattled President General of the Ohanaeze Ndigbo, Chief John Nnia Nwodo at Ukehe in Enugu State, was on Sunday rocked by bomb blast. According to the Enugu State Police, the blast emanated from an Improvised Explosive Device, IED, which was thrown into his house by unknown persons from outside his compound.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The explosion, which destroyed part of his building, left the the ceiling and windows of the house shattered.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Media Adviser to the President General, Chief Emeka Attamah, who confirmed the attack said that the Enugu State Commissioner of Police, Danmallam Mohammed, accompanied by the Area Commander for Nsukka Police Command and the Divisional Police Officer for Igbo Etiti LGA, were there to inspect the scene of the blast which created a crater in the compound.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Addressing the people who tripped to Chief Nwodoâ€™s home, the Commissioner enjoined them to always be vigilant and to report any strange faces to security operatives.\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-04-29 13:59:01', 'APPROVED'),
(54, 7, '54.jpg', 'Court Orders Interim Forfeiture Of Patience Jonathan&rsquo;s Properties In Abuja', '\n<p>\n   The Federal High Court sitting in Abuja on Monday ordered an interim forfeiture of two properties linked to the wife of former President Goodluck Jonathan, Patience Jonathan. In a Ruling on an ex parte application filed by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), the trial judge Justice Nnamdi Dimgba dismissed Mrs Jonathanâ€™s objection to the application for lacking in merit.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   Justice Dimgba also ruled that the order will only last for 45 days.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   He added that within the 45 days, The EFCC must conclude its investigations and charge the suspects being investigated in respect of the alleged crimes linked to properties.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   He, however, added that the EFCC was at liberty to file an application for the extension of the lifespan of the order before the expiration of the initial 45 days.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   He also ordered that if for any reason EFCCâ€™s officials needed to access the properties within the period of interim forfeiture, they must do so with the respondents in attendance.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   He also ordered that the inventory of the fixtures in the properties and a report must be submitted to the court.\r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   \r\n</p>\n\n<p>\n   The properties located in Abuja are said to be held in the name of Ariwabai Aruera Reachout Foundation, which Mrs Jonathan is said to be one of its â€œtrustees.â€  The EFCC had, in an ex parte application filed in September last year, asked for an interim forfeiture of the properties, which it claimed were subjects of an ongoing criminal investigation.\n</p>\n', 6, '2018-05-01 04:52:16', 'APPROVED');
